The paper also discusses variance-reduction stochastic methods and optimization techniques, which are relevant to machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions information theory and signal processing, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) respectively, making them less likely but still possible sub-categories.
